Prerequisites:
--------------

  Python packages:
    numpy
    scipy
    matplotlib (required for the 'plot' module)
    progressbar2 (if you want to see a progress indicator)

  Libraries:
    GSL development package (libgsl0-dev?) - for the interpolation module
    netcdf shared library - to read/write netcdf files
    lapack shared library (version 3), for the EOF module

Optional:
---------
  Python packages:
    cartopy (map projections; -- or --)
    basemap (matplotlib toolkit, for overlaying maps and doing projections)


To install:
-----------

  python setup.py build
  python setup.py install

If the build process fails, check if you have all the prerequisites.



If you want to run the package without installing first:
--------------------------------------------------------

1) Run 'python setup.py build_ext --inplace'
2) Add this directory to your PYTHONPATH

